# Photographs are binary. Git normally detects this on its own, but a single
# line-ending "fix" applied to a JPEG corrupts it silently — the file keeps the
# right name and roughly the right size, and you only find out when a
# photograph fails to decode in someone's browser. Declaring it costs nothing
# and removes the possibility.
*.jpg   binary
*.JPG   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.JPEG  binary
*.png   binary
*.PNG   binary
*.avif  binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
